- Lawrence Poe<br>
<br>
1) We can rule out this assumption that grouping is required to prevent people from spamming others with requester boxes.  Although it less mana than a rez, it isn't super cheap mana-wise.  I think this reason was only given as a very poor excuse just to get the programmers out of another fix, so that they can get on with Luclin.  They might lose me as a customer before Luclin even comes out if excuses like this are used too often.<br>
2) If they are going to stick with the lame excuse outlined above, then they should put a grouping requirement into the resurrection spells.  You don't even need to be in the same zone as somebody to spam them if you have a rez spell!  Wow!  Of course I've never been spammed by a rezzer before, for the same reason I'll never be spammed by a translocator: mana cost.  I bet clerics won't be happy if they add a grouping requirement to rezzes.<br>
3) When you translocate somebody, and they zone, the grouping bug is nearly inevitable without careful planning.  If you weren't grouped with the person in the first place, this problem would be eliminated.<br>
<br>
Nyargle Fizzlekins <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 11:27:19 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm...</span><hr size=1> It would be more work for them to wait until people complained and petitioned.  So instead of doing that, they avoid the &quot;non-group&quot; functionality all together.  But still, at least rezzes still have the confirm.  Mages are getting away with murder still haveing a non confirmed CoH.  i.e.  Trying to zone out and getting summoned back to the mage.  Since I am the CoH link person, the mage KNOWS I can't disband because that would break the link.  I've been on the brunt end of pranks before.  No I just keep in mind to disband IMMEDIATELY when I leave a group that has a CoH mage in it.  Easy way to avoid their smug, childish, pranks.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nyargle>Nyargle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 11:34:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmmm...</span><hr size=1> I agree, CoH should be the spell with a grouping requirement (mostly for targetting reasons) AND a confirm dialog.  With translocate it's just plain stupid having a confirm dialog since you have to have the player standing within range anyways, and can just target them... what kind of moron spends 200 mana a pop to spam somebody? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 1:07:06 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well...</span><hr size=1> I guess a person with little or nothing to do on their hands.  I left bristlebane because of such a person.  Was verbally abused for a LONG time.  And I know, you say, just put him on your ignore list.  The person would keep creating new accounts with a brand new level one so I could not keep up.  It got to the point were my level 52 Cleric wasn't even worth it anymore.  So I left.  There ARE people like that out there, and it is completely sad.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugraffenlaff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graffenlaff</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=img src= http://graffenlaff.homestead.com/files/grafflogo.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 1:30:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> The scenario seems that VI is more focused on what makes their job easier - in comparison to what makes the game more fluid.<br>
<br>
If spamming is the issue, then the solution should be player notifies GM, GM investigates and if necessary abusers of these potential misuses of the game should have their accounts closed. That of course means they have to take an active role in administrating a positive gaming environment.<br>
<br>
Day 1 of the new conformation box - hate raid, a player (tank) fell asleep. Luckily he had a druid in his group to port him out to a relatively safe area - relatively, not guaranteed, since it wasn't to his bind point in a city.<br>
<br>
BTW - argumentatively, a cleric could only spam you if there was a rezzible body to target.<br>
<br>
 <p>"Humbly but never humbled"<p>
<b>Graffenlaff Delaffensa</b><br><i>
Tunare's Channeler<br>
Triad Continuum</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 2:03:15 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thank goodness...</span><hr size=1> Thank goodness my new family on Cazic is so wonderful.  Truly helps me forget how horrible the situation was and how inept the guides, GM's, or VI in general were at dealing with the problem.  You may wonder why I have such a horrible attitude towards them sometimes.  There you have it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
W.F.<br>
<br>
I sometimes need to remember not to take it out on other people.  And to all of them, I apologize most sincerely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulamil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lamil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/01 10:21:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Grouping for TL</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think the grouping and confirmation boxes are not a bad idea with the new 'push' spells. You can now cast Translocate: Combine, say, in a full group. Anyone who wants to go to combine (the person leaving the group) will hit yes, anyone who doesn't will hit no (the rest of the group). So there is now no disbanding to port someone out.<br>
<br>
Lamil Ro`Jetthe<br>
52 Wiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/01 10:33:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping for TL</span><hr size=1> Someone suggested a very good idea for the confirmation boxes: have them default to yes with a 30 second timer.  If you are asleep you'll STILL port off, but it still controls the trick of sending someone off maliciously. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 11:37:39 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> indeed...</span><hr size=1> I have heard similar.  And I think it is the solution.  Seems almost TOO logical.  Hope they can get their minds around it.  And forgive the attitude.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nyargle>Nyargle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 12:38:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> grouping?</span><hr size=1> Hey Lamil, there isn't a 'translocate group: combine' it's only 'translocate: combine'.<br>
You have to target the player you want to send to dreadlands anyways, having them grouped simply makes it a hassle to remove them from the group.<br>
<br>
One way to escape from the grouping bug messing things up is to cast translocate on a group member, and disband them before they hit the yes button to confirm.  I haven't really confirmed that this works well, but it seemed to work for me the first time I did it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=215.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=200.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=178.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.threadControl?topicID=178.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=178.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=178.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffes